description: From the verb phrase speed up.

entries.meaning: An amount or rate of decrease in time taken to do a certain amount of work.
examples: The results of this generalized speedup of the corporate metabolism are multiple: shorter product life cycles, more leasing and renting, more frequent buying and selling, more ephemeral consumption patterns,  [â€¦]

entries.meaning: (chiefly computing) The relationship between time taken and number of processors used.
(labor, politics) An employer's demand for more output without more pay.
